Kraus Music Products Home Page





   
                                                               
 
Kraus Music Products, 
    Inc. is one of the largest suppliers in the world of pads, cork, felt, and 
    other component parts used in wind musical instrument repair.

 We are a wholesale 
    supplier only to music repair businesses.  
    Sorry, but we don't sell to individual schools, teachers, or musicians.  
    If you need a small quantity of parts for your own instruments, we suggest 
    you contact a local music repair shop.  Lists of repair shops and other 
    information for the public can be found at www.napbirt.org.
KMP is no longer a tool 
    company. We are now focused only on our core business which is supplying repair 
    shops and manufacturers with the highest quality pads, cork, synthetic pads, 
    synthetic valve felts, new materials for key corks and silencers, glues, solder, 
    and similar products.
 
May 
    2017 New Step Bevel Synthetic Pad
We now make 
    OmniPads 
    in two styles, the classic Taper Radius style and a new Step Bevel Style. 
    Taper Radius pads are labeled OmniPad 
    TR and Step Bevel Pads are OmniPad 
    SB. The new Step Bevel pads have the step bevel machined into the hard plastic 
    backer which fully supports the foam layer, and the proportions and shape 
    are similar to our 101 Clarinet pads.

We will have 
    more technical information available soon, but you can call us now to ask 
    about all the synthetic pad options. Don't forget the non beveled EZ Pads 
    are made from the same cushion and sealing layer foams, and are an equally 
    valid pad at a much lower price so long as your key cup is large enough for 
    a non beveled pad to cover the tonehole.
    
